This part of code deal with systematic uncertainty of vertex reconstruction
The general logic is:

- First get a TrackMover ntuple:
  python ntuple.py submit
  python mltruth.py submit

- Base on the ntuple, get histograms:
  python hists.submit.py 
  ./mctruth.exe -s

- Get vertex reconstruction efficiency plot:
  python draw.py TM_config20_tau000030000um /uscms/home/pkotamni/nobackup/crabdirs/TrackMoverHistsULV30Lepmv2_20_tau000030000um/SingleLepton2017.root /uscms/home/pkotamni/nobackup/crabdirs/TrackMoverHistsULV30Lepmv2_20_tau000030000um/background_leptonpresel_2017.root
  python ploteff.py
